CHEESE TWISTS 🧀 This has to be one of my favourite things to get at Sainsbury's or Lidl bakery! You can mix this up and add pesto, tomato sauce, make it sweet, make them small or big! Ingredients 1 sheet puff pastry 2 eggs, beaten 2tsp dijon mustard Lots of grated cheddar and parmesan Salt and pepper Garlic powder and mixed herbs, optional* Method • Mix mustard, salt and pepper with the eggs, add garlic and mixed herbs for extra flavour. • Brush onto the puff pastry, save some to brush on the cheese twists just before baking. • Sprinkle on the grated cheddar and parmesan. • Fold, flatten and cut into strips as shown in the reel, then twist. I made 5 but I should have made 6 or 7 because they were bigger than what I expected • Brush on some more egg wash on each of them. • Follow cooking guidelines on puff pastry packaging or cooking for about 15-20minutes until golden! Have you noticed your skin getting darker despite having a skincare routine? 😩 There could be several reasons why your skin is getting darker 😭after using skincare products: 📌Photosensitivity: Some skincare products, especially those containing certain active ingredients like retinoids or alpha hydroxy acids, can make your skin more sensitive to UV radiation. Without proper sun protection, this increased sensitivity can lead to sun-induced skin darkening. 📌Allergic Reactions: Your skin might react adversely to certain ingredients in skincare products, causing irritation, inflammation, and hyperpigmentation, which can result in a darker appearance. 📌Inflammation: Skincare products that are too harsh or abrasive can irritate the skin, leading to inflammation and potential darkening as a response to this irritation. 📌Chemical Peels or Exfoliants: Overusing chemical peels, exfoliants, or other potent treatments can damage the skin’s barrier and result in darkening, especially if not used as directed. 📌Improper Application: Using skin care products incorrectly or not following recommended instructions can lead to adverse effects, including skin darkening. 📌Mismatched Products: Using skincare products that are not suitable for your specific skin type or concerns can exacerbate skin issues and potentially lead to darkening. 📌Lack of Sun Protection: Even if your skincare routine involves products that increase skin sensitivity to the sun, failing to use sunscreen daily can contribute to skin darkening. It’s crucial to choose skincare products carefully, perform patch tests when introducing new products, follow usage instructions, and consistently use sunscreen to mitigate the risk of skin darkening as a result of your skincare routine. If you notice persistent darkening or adverse reactions, consult a dermatologist for guidance. Thank you for watching. MARISRIE.SKIN
